est or wedges.","<strong>Raspberry swirl cheesecake:<\/strong> after <b>step 7,<b> clean the mixing bowl. Place <b>150 g raspberries<b> in mixing bowl and blend <b><strong>30 sec\/speed 10.<\/strong><b> Pass purée through a fine sieve into a bowl. Stir <b>2 tbsp sugar<b> into purée and drop purée onto unbaked cheesecake with a teaspoon. Swirl sauce into filling with a wooden skewer or cocktail stick. Bake as directed in the recipe.","Cooling the cake slowly in the oven helps prevent surface cracks. If a crack does form, you can disguise it with one of the following: a dusting of icing sugar, whipped cream, caramel sauce, chocolate sauce or fruit coulis."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","7h 20m","12 slices"]}